children.text: The layers of trench mesh have now been lapped sufficiently at their joins.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 2870 Residential Slabs and Footings states in section 5.3.2 Reinforcement that
‘Trench mesh shall be spliced, where necessary, by a lap of 500 mm’.
All of the trench mesh steel reinforcement laps have been checked. Any areas where deficiencies were identified have been addressed, with the area ready for concrete to be poured.
